\taxon{Example}
\title{The theory of a point does not have an initial model.}
\import{prelude}

\p{As [sets are theories](001D), we might try to produce a point of any set via the following definition.}

\pre{%
\kw{ind} \kw{def} something-from-nothing (A : Set) : A := \kw{init} A
}

\p{However, this would make Coln inconsistent by allowing us to produce a point in the [empty set](001Q).}
